00:00:57.329 --> 00:01:01.000
The ancient Romans definitely celebrated birthdays,
though, and were probably the first people

00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:05.320
to celebrate their family and friends birthdays,
not just those of rulers and gods.

00:01:05.320 --> 00:01:10.130
In Denmark, a Danish flag placed outside the
home means that it's somebody's birthday.

00:01:10.130 --> 00:01:14.409
If it's a child's birthday, the presents are
usually placed on or around the child's bed

00:01:14.409 --> 00:01:16.690
so they can wake up surrounded by presents.

00:01:16.690 --> 00:01:17.690
That's nice!

00:01:17.690 --> 00:01:21.160
Sometimes a "cake man" or "cake lady" is served,
depending on whether the party is for a boy

00:01:21.160 --> 00:01:22.160
or a girl.

00:01:22.160 --> 00:01:26.420
The head of the cake person is usually chopped
off first, which I will now demonstrate.

